
Overview of noun gambit

The noun gambit has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. gambit, ploy -- (an opening remark intended to secure an advantage for the speaker)
2. ploy, gambit, stratagem -- (a maneuver in a game or conversation)
3. gambit -- (a chess move early in the game in which the player sacrifices minor pieces in order to obtain an advantageous position)
